  "texts": [
    "Although RoboRXN has demonstrated the ability to perform most tasks in chemical and material synthesis, the hardware currently cannot perform product purification and multistep synthesis continuously.",
    "HTE using flow platformsFlow reactions are characterized by a constant flow of reagents and products into and out of the reaction vessel.",
    "A flow platform consists of a fluid delivery system, mixing tools, reactors, quenching units, pressure regulation units, and collection vessels.",
    "The fluid delivery is normally executed using either high-pressure liquid chromatography (HPLC), a syringe, or peristaltic pumps.",
    "A passive mixing stage where the reagents are introduced to the system through a Y-or T-connection is the most common approach observed for most flow reactions, while more specialized mixing tools can be incorporated depending on the reaction prerequisites."
  ],
